HEADWORD: Arreptitious
<hw>Ar`rep*ti"tious</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>arreptitius</ets>.]</ety> <def>Snatched away; seized or possessed,
as a demoniac; raving; mad; crack-brained.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Odd, <qex>arreptitious</qex>, frantic extravagances.</q>
<rj><qau>Howell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

